Archaeologists found evidence that Neanderthals lived alongside predators in a cave in Spain 200,000 years ago . 
  Fossilised remains of cave bears and badgers were found in the Cave of Llenes near Senterada in Catalonia . 
  Other canivores including hyenas and leopards were also living in the cave . 
  Archaeologists also found evidence of Neanderthal camps and stone tools . 
  The cave is in the foothills of the Pyrenees Mountains in Spain . 
 